            <h1>Final project proposal</h1>
            
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            
            <p>SLO Groove</p>
            
            <p>SLO Groove is a fictional dance studio. It is located in downtown San Luis Obispo, California on Broad Street. It first opened in 2018 as a small business, and has grown into a much larger community over the last few years. SLO Groove offers a variety of genres of dance, and welcomes all age groups! We are open Monday-Saturday, and closed on Sunday.</p>
            
            <h2>Target audience</h2>
            
            <p>We hope to bring in anyone who has a passion for dance or wants to be acitve! We offer hip-hop, jazz, ballet, modern, tap, and zumba classes. There is something for all ages. You first class is on us! We also offer student discounts for Cal Poly and Cuesta students if they sign up for a month of classes. There are classes for beginners, intermediate, and advanced dancers. If you are not sure of your own skill level, we can help assess what classes are best for you! </p>
           
            <p>The primary tasks and goals of using our website is to be able to understand what classes we offer, the times classes start and end, check out the instructors, and understand who we are as a company. The website also allows dancers to reserve spots in classes because we have reduced the amount of dancers that are allowed in a class due to COVID-19 guidelines. Through our website dancers can gain knowledge of the different genres we offer at the studio and how we are doing our best to keep each other safe by enforcing stict COVID-19 guidelines. </p>
            
