                    <h2>Kailey Cruz</h2>
				
					<p>Kailey grew up as a competitive dancer at Santa Barbara Performing Arts Center. She began teaching as a teenager, and continued to teach as she pursued her degree in Human Development and Elementary Education. During college she also competed in jazz and hip hop groups. After college, Kailey began teahcing at an elementary school in San Luis Obispo, and teahces Jazz on the side. Dance has always been a constant in Kailey's life so she decided to continuing teaching what she enjoys as well as being a full-time school teacher. </p>
        
                <p>    [Jules Marchant headshot.] </p>
                
                 <h2>Jules Marchant</h2>
				
					<p>Julesâ€™ love for dance started at at SLO Movement Arts Center at the age of 5. She continued studying Ballet, Tap, Jazz, Modern and Lyrical at Cal State Long Beach. After graduating Cal State Long Beach, Julia trained with Ballet Master Alfredo Corvino of the Metropolitan Opera Ballet. Jules decided to return to San Luis Obispo after her time on the road, and began teaching at SLO Groove and other studios for the last 10 years. She teahces both Ballet and Tap.</p>
			    
                <p>    [Dave Martin headshot.] </p>
                
                 <h2>Dave Martin</h2>
				
					<p>Dave is a San Diego native. He has traveld and been on tour with numerious Pop and Hip Hop artists as a background dancer. He has been a prominent figure in the hip hop industry for over 10 years now. His love for movement and groove have allowed him to soar in the industry. He recently moved to San Luis Obispo, and is excited to share his love for dance and teacher younger ancers what it takes to make it in such a competitve industry. Dave is our hip hop instructor. </p>
                
